<p>March 17, 2020 (Mayfield KY) In accordance with recommendations of the Center for Disease Control, and in pursuance of the most recent guidance from the office of the Governor on March 17, 2020, and to promote the well-being of the citizens of Mayfield, City Hall will be closing to the public <b>beginning at 8 a.m. on Thursday, March 19, 2020.</b></p>

<p>All city departments will remain responsive to our citizens' needs through e-mail, the US Postal Service, and telephone @ (270) 247-1981. City Administrative employees will be available during regular business hours 8:00 a.m. - 4:30 p.m. All public parks will be closed and all scheduled events in the parks are cancelled.</p>

<hr>
<br><p><b>Message from the Mayfield City Clerk:</b><br>
City hall is closed to the public. Delinquent property taxes may be paid by mail or online but must be paid by March 31 to avoid publication and the tax sale. You may renew your business license by mail with required paperwork however, the April 15 business licenses deadline, will be extended in accordance with the new IRS deadline of July 15. Our staff is at work and available by telephone, 270-247-1981.</p>
<span class="pf5">Tamie Johnson</span><br>
Mayfield City Clerk


